cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Structural Invariance of Return Skewness in Football Betting Markets"
message: "If you use this study, data pipeline, or findings, please cite it."
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: Vitor
    family-names: Alves
    affiliation: "Cold Code Labs"
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX"  # TODO: register at orcid.org, uncomment & fill before release
repository-code: "https://github.com/cold-code-labs/skew-dynamic"
url: "https://skew-dynamic.coldcodelabs.com"
# doi: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"  # minted by Zenodo on the first GitHub release
abstract: >-
  An open empirical study by Cold Code Labs showing that the skewness of returns
  implied by football betting markets is a structural invariant: ~100% the
  within-match Bernoulli asymmetry of the win-probability distribution (the
  favourite-longshot bias), with a league-level value fixed by sporting
  competitiveness — a relation that survives a competitiveness measure built
  without odds — and no secular drift within the modern competitive regime.
keywords:
  - skewness
  - favourite-longshot bias
  - betting markets
  - market efficiency
  - implied probabilities
  - structural invariance
  - competitive balance
